    "A perfect field K is called Kummer-faithful if, for any semiabelian variety A over a finite extension L of K, the Mordell-Weil group A(L) has trivial divisible part (for more detail, see Definition 1.1).",
    "In this paper, we obtain a wide class of Kummer-faithful fields that are not sub-p-adic (see Definition 1.1 for the definition).",
    "This improves some of the previous results by Ozeki-Taguchi [OT22] and by Ohtani [Oht22] (see also its corrigendum [Oht23]).",
    "The notion of Kummer-faithfulness (resp.",
    "sub-p-adicness) originates from anabelian geometry and it is expected (resp."
